<!DOCTYPE chapter SYSTEM "cruise_help.dtd">
<chapter title="See artifacts as sub-tabs">
  <p>After <cref topic="dev_upload_test_report">uploading html reports</cref>, it is often useful to be able to easily view this information when trying to <cref topic="dev_understand_why_build_broken">understand why the build is broken</cref>.</p>
  <section title="Example usage">
    <bullets>
      <item>Suppose we have configured Go to <cref topic="dev_upload_test_report">upload a flash video and html file and display it as a tab</cref></item>
      <item>Click on the <cref topic="Pipelines_Dashboard_page">Pipelines</cref> tab</item>
      <img src="resources/images/cruise/topnav_pipelines.png" />
      <item>Click on the stage you want to investigate</item>
      <img src="resources/images/cruise/dev/see_artifact_as_tab/click_on_stage.png"/>
      <item>Click on the job you want to investigate</item>
      <img src="resources/images/cruise/dev/see_artifact_as_tab/2_click_job_with_tab.png" />
      <item>Click on the tab you created</item>
      <img src="resources/images/cruise/dev/see_artifact_as_tab/3_click_my_subtab.png" />
      <item>Clicking on the tab will load the page, which will start the video!</item>
      <item>To view the content in a new window, just click "Download Recording"</item>
      <img src="resources/images/cruise/dev/see_artifact_as_tab/4_download_content.png" />
    </bullets>
  </section>
</chapter>
